  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Mrs. Sarah Blake Sturgis Shaw thanks Maria Weston Chapman for the Liberty Bell. Mrs. Shaw writes: &quot;I think the Fair here was a failure---I furnished over 100 dollars of articles, but few were sold.&quot; She asks how Maria W. Chapman feels about her country now. Mrs. Shaw gives an enthusiastic description of a recently arrived grandson. She asks if Maria W. Chapman&apos;s sisters are still in Itialy and if Lucia Weston is getting well in &quot;dear old Rome.&quot;</subfield>
